---
layout: page
nohero: true
image: /vs/images/flowfuse-vs-litmus-hero.png
imageDescription: "FlowFuse vs Litmus Hero Image"
heroTitle: "A Flexible Alternative to <span class='text-red-600'>Litmus</span>"
meta:
    title: "A Flexible Alternative to Litmus"
    description: "FlowFuse is an open, cloud-ready platform that industrial teams choose as an alternative to Litmus. Build faster, stay flexible, and scale Industrial AI on your terms — without unnecessary lock-in."
hero:
    buttonText: "Talk to a Migration Expert"
    buttonLink: "https://meetings-eu1.hubspot.com/michael-davis/round-robin-michael-omar-kasheef?utm_campa[…]113138546&utm_content=113138546&utm_source=hs_automation"
    buttonReference: "vs-litmus"
sectionTitle: "Why Industrial Teams Consider <span class='text-red-600'>FlowFuse Instead of Litmus</span>"
sectionSubtitle: "Open, flexible edge architecture. Reduced vendor lock-in and higher portability."
sections:
    - svgPath: "components/icons/cube-transparent.svg"
      title: "Built for open architectures"
      description: "Run your Industrial IoT and AI workloads at the edge, on-premise, or in the cloud, leveraging maximum flexibility for deployment."
    - svgPath: "components/icons/squares-plus.svg"
      title: "Open & extensible"
      description: "Built on open-source Node-RED so engineering teams can integrate a wide range of OT assets, IT systems, and AI services with full visibility into every flow."
    - svgPath: "components/icons/link.svg"
      title: "Fast integrations"
      description: "Accelerate time from prototype to production and eliminate glue code with native support for MQTT, OPC-UA, REST APIs, SQL targets, and UNS-style architectures."
table:
    - feature: "Foundation & Governance"
      flowFuse: "<span class='font-medium'>Open-source (Node-RED).</span> Full transparency with human-readable JSON flows. Users own, inspect, and govern every line of logic."
      litmus: "<span class='font-medium'>Proprietary</span>. All-in-one 'black box' stack. Governance and visibility are limited to what the vendor's tools allow."
    - feature: "Deployment & Extensibility"
      flowFuse: "<span class='font-medium'>Infrastructure agnostic.</span> Runs on edge, cloud, or on-prem. Extendable via plain JavaScript/APIs; your team owns the logic."
      litmus: "<span class='font-medium'>Platform-dictated.</span> Optimized for large rollouts, but architectural decisions and customization are bounded by the ecosystem."
    - feature: "Integration & Connectivity"
      flowFuse: "<span class='font-medium'>Unrestricted.</span> 5,000+ community nodes + native MQTT, OPC-UA, and UNS. Connect to anything without vendor roadmaps."
      litmus: "<span class='font-medium'>Pre-built.</span> Offers connectors for major platforms, but limited to the specific integrations Litmus has prioritized."
    - feature: "Industrial AI Strategy"
      flowFuse: "<span class='font-medium'>Agnostic.</span> Bring your own models and services. Your AI strategy remains flexible as the market evolves."
      litmus: "<span class='font-medium'>Opinionated.</span> Fast to start with an integrated stack, but your AI choices are tied to the vendor's specific roadmap."
    - feature: "Vendor Lock-in Risk"
      flowFuse: "<span class='font-medium'>Zero.</span> Fully portable, version-controlled code that is never held hostage by a single vendor."
      litmus: "<span class='font-medium'>High.</span> Requires full buy-in to a single vendor stack for connectivity, analytics, and AI."
switch:
    title: How to Move Workloads <span class='text-red-600'>from Litmus to FlowFuse</span>
    content:
        - "<span class='font-semibold'>Migration consultation:</span> We review your current Litmus deployment and data flows to propose a FlowFuse architecture that preserves requirements while increasing openness."
        - "<span class='font-semibold'>Try FlowFuse with your data:</span> Connect your OT assets and replicate key pipelines in a controlled pilot to verify performance and operator experience before you commit."
        - "<span class='font-semibold'>Gradual rollout with expert support:</span> We provide expert support from the initial pilot through multi-site rollout, helping your team standardize patterns and train engineers."
    cta: TALK TO A MIGRATION EXPERT
    ctaUrl: "/book-demo"
cta:
    title: "Exploring Alternatives to Litmus?"
    content: "Discover how FlowFuse can help your team modernize its industrial edge and data infrastructure with an open, flexible platform that complements your existing AI and analytics strategy. <a href='https://meetings-eu1.hubspot.com/michael-davis/round-robin-michael-omar-kasheef?utm_campa[…]113138546&utm_content=113138546&utm_source=hs_automation' class='font-semibold'>Book a Demo with a FlowFuse Expert</a>."
---
<!--Hero Content-->
<div class="w-full px-6">
    <div class="w-full pt-12 pb-20 md:pt-6 md:pb-8">
        <div class="md:flex md:my-16 items-center md:flex-row md:justify-between container mx-auto text-center md:text-left md:max-w-screen-lg gap-8 items-stretch">
            <div class="m-auto md:w-1/2">
                <h1 class="w-full mt-0 m-auto">
                    {{ heroTitle | safe }}
                </h1>
                <p class="mb-10">
                    {{ meta.description }}
                </p>
                <div class="md:mt-3 gap-4 hidden md:flex md:flex-row md:inline md:items-start md:justify-start md:m-0">    
                    {% macro migrationExpertButton(desktop=true) %}
                    <a class="ff-btn ff-btn--highlight text-base flex inline uppercase {% if desktop %}min-h-[40px]{% else %}w-full m-auto mt-12{% endif %}" 
                        href="{{ hero.buttonLink }}" 
                        onclick="capture('talk-to-migration-expert', {'reference': '{{ hero.buttonReference }}'})">
                        {{ hero.buttonText }}
                    </a>
                    {% endmacro %}
                    {{ migrationExpertButton() }}
                    {% macro tryItOutButton(desktop=true) %}
                    <a class="ff-btn uppercase text-base {% if desktop %}inline{% else %}flex flex-col w-full m-auto sm:mt-12{% endif %}" 
                    href="{% include "sign-up-url.njk" %}" 
                    onclick="capture('try-it-out', {'reference': '{{ hero.buttonReference }}'})">
                        <span class="flex gap-2 uppercase items-center text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-800">
                            TRY IT OUT
                            {% include "components/icons/arrow-right.svg" %}
                        </span>
                    </a>
                    {% endmacro %}
                    {{ tryItOutButton() }}
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-1/2 flex-grow relative">
                <div class="ff-image-cover ff-image-rounded w-full h-full border border-red-600">
                    {% set imageSrc = ["./", image ] | join %}
                    {% image imageSrc, imageDescription, [496] %}           
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row md:hidden gap-3">
                {{ migrationExpertButton(false) }}
                {{ tryItOutButton(false) }}
            </div>
        </div>   
    </div>
    <div class="max-w-screen-lg mx-auto">
        <!-- Cards -->  
        {% set blueCards = [
            {"title": "Open, flexible edge architecture",
            "content": "Customers can run FlowFuse where it makes sense — <span class='font-medium'>at the edge, on-premises, or in the cloud</span> — and integrate with a wide range of clouds, data platforms, and AI services, rather than a single, tightly coupled stack."},
            {"title": "Reduced vendor lock-in and higher portability",
            "content": "Because flows remain Node-RED-compatible and <span class='font-medium'>rely on open standards</span>, organizations can evolve their Industrial AI strategy over time without being constrained by a monolithic, proprietary edge data platform."}
        ] %}
        <div class="mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 text-center md:text-left mb-20">
            {% for card in blueCards %}
            <div class="p-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-white to-indigo-50 border border-indigo-100 rounded-lg">
                <h5 class="text-indigo-600">{{ card.title }}</h5>
                <p>{{ card.content | safe }}</p>
            </div>
            {% endfor %}
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="w-full px-6 bg-indigo-50/50 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-screen-lg mx-auto">
        <!-- From Litmus to FlowFuse -->  
        <h2 class="text-center w-full md:text-left">{{ sectionTitle | safe }}</h2>
        <p>Industrial organizations evaluating Litmus often explore FlowFuse for a more open, modular approach to edge connectivity, data orchestration, and Industrial AI workloads.​</p>
        <div class="w-full grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-x-8 gap-y-14 mt-16">
            {% for section in sections %}
            <div class="relative w-full max-md:max-w-md mx-auto">
                <div class="flex flex-col items-center sm:items-start">
                    <div class="flex flex-col justify-center md:justify-start gap-3 w-full">
                        <div class="w-12 h-12 m-auto sm:m-0 rounded-full bg-red-400/70 text-white flex items-center justify-center">
                            <div class="w-5 h-5">
                                {% include section.svgPath %}
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="w-full flex flex-row gap-3 mx-auto md:m-0">
                            <h5 class="w-full md:m-0">
                                <div class="text-xl text-gray-600 text-center sm:text-left">{{ section.title }}</div>
                            </h5>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p class="text-center sm:text-left font-light">{{ section.description | safe }}</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            {% endfor %}
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="w-full px-6 py-20">
    <div class="max-w-screen-lg mx-auto">        
        <!-- Table Section -->
        <div>
            <span class="inline-block rounded bg-indigo-50 px-3 py-1 text-xs text-gray-700 max-md:block max-md:w-fit max-md:mx-auto">Comparison</span>
            <h2 class="mt-4 mb-8 max-md:text-center"><span class="text-red-600">FlowFuse and Litmus</span> at a Glance</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="relative overflow-x-auto rounded-lg border border-indigo-600">
            <table class="w-full table-fixed min-w-[500px]">
                <thead class="bg-indigo-100 text-indigo-900">
                    <tr>
                        <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3 w-1/3">
                            Features
                        </th>
                        <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3 w-1/3">
                            FlowFuse (Open &amp; Flexible)
                        </th>
                        <th scope="col" class="px-6 py-3 w-1/3">
                            Litmus (Proprietary &amp; Unified)
                        </th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    {% for item in table %}
                    <tr class="even:bg-indigo-50/50 border-t border-indigo-200">
                        <th scope="row" class="px-6 py-4 font-medium text-center">
                            {{ item.feature }}
                        </th>
                        <td class="px-6 py-4 font-light">
                            {{ item.flowFuse | safe }}
                        </td>
                        <td class="px-6 py-4 font-light">
                            {{ item.litmus | safe }}
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    {% endfor %}
                </tbody>
            </table>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="w-full px-6 py-20 bg-[radial-gradient(ellipse_120%_120%_at_50%_120%,theme(colors.indigo.600)_0%,theme(colors.indigo.900)_100%)]">
    <div class="max-w-screen-lg mx-auto">
        <!-- Switch Section -->
        <div class="container p-8 md:max-w-screen-lg border border-red-200 rounded-lg bg-white drop-shadow-lg m-auto grid max-sm:grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-[minmax(500px,_1fr) 1fr 1fr] sm:grid-flow-col sm:gap-x-6 sm:grid-rows-[[minmax(100px,_1fr)_minmax(20px,_1fr)]">
            <h3 class="order-1 max-sm:text-center">{{ switch.title | safe }}</h3>
            <div class="sm:row-span-2 sm:col-span-2 sm:order-3 order-2 flex items-center max-sm:pl-6 max-sm:my-4 sm:px-10 m-auto">
                <ol class="list-decimal mt-2">
                {% for item in switch.content %}
                <li class="{% if not loop.last %}mb-4{%endif%}">{{ item | safe}}</li>
                {% endfor %}
                </ol>
            </div>
            <div class="flex sm:items-end justify-start sm:order-2 order-3 sm:self-end max-sm:mt-6 max-sm:mx-auto">
                {{ migrationExpertButton() }}
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>    
<div class="w-full px-6 pb-24">
    <p class="text-center md:max-w-screen-lg m-auto mt-24 font-medium text-indigo-900">Trusted by industrial teams worldwide to modernize their OT‑IT data infrastructure and edge architectures.</p>
    <!-- Social proof -->
    <div class="max-w-md sm:max-w-screen-lg m-auto max-w-5xl mb-14">
        <div class="mx-auto w-full">
            {% include "social-proof.njk" %}
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- CTA section -->
    <div class="ff-blue-card text-center w-full md:text-left md:max-w-screen-lg mx-auto mt-6 flex flex-col gap-6">
        <h2 class="text-indigo-600">{{ cta.title | safe }}</h2>
        <p>{{ cta.content | safe }}</p>
    </div>
</div>
